# qdc-sched (starter)

Phase 1 implemented:
- QPU state (topology + reservations) with spatial concurrency
- Circuit profiling
- Plan-A (no cutting) vs Wait planner
- SABRE-based mapping restricted to a chosen physical qubit subset
- Aer execution with toggleable fidelity estimation (ideal vs noisy) and proxy fidelity

Next phases (interfaces already scaffolded):
- Circuit cutting addon baseline strategy
- FitCut-style scheduler-aware cutting strategy
- OBP-assisted expectation estimation (toggle)

## Quick start

```bash
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e .
python -m qdc_sched.demo.run_demo
```

If you want IBM Fake backends:
```bash
pip install -e ".[ibm]"
```
